HEADWORD: Morgan
<hw>Mor"gan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One
of a celebrated breed of small compact American saddle and trotting
horses; -- so called from the name of the stud (Justin Morgan) from
which the breed originated in Vermont.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

